Name: Parasal-650
Uses: Headache, muscle aches, arthritis, backache, toothaches, colds, fevers and mild arthritis
Side Effects: Hives, difficulty breathing,swelling of your face, lips, tongue, or throat

Name: Hydrochlorothiazide
Uses: Edema (fluid retention; excess fluid held in body tissues),rid of unneeded water and salt from the body into the urine
Side Effects: Upset stomach, dizziness, or headache may occur as your body adjusts to the medication

Name: Digene
Uses: Indigestion, extra gas, bloating, belching and feeling of discomfort in the stomach or gut
Side Effects: The most common side effects observed with this medicine include nausea, headache, dizziness, flatulence, diarrhea, and stomach pain, vomiting

Name: Multivitamin
Uses: Vitamin and mineral deficiency and acts as an immunity booster in adults.
Side Effects: Nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, and upset stomach may be seen as side effects

Name: Calcium
Uses: Bone loss (osteoporosis),  weak bones (osteomalacia/rickets), decreased activity of the parathyroid gland (hypoparathyroidism),   certain muscle disease (latent tetany)
Side Effects: Calcium supplements may increase the incidence of constipation, severe diarrhea, abdominal pain

Name: Cetrizine
Uses: Watery eyes, runny nose, itching eyes/nose, sneezing, hives, and itching,  blockes a certain natural substance (histamine)
Side Effects: Some drowsiness, excessive tirednessdry mouth, stomach pain, diarrhea, vomiting

Name: Dextromethorphan
Uses: Relieve cough caused by the common cold, the flu, or other conditions.
Side Effects: Slight drowsiness/dizziness, nausea, or vomiting may occur.

Name: Curcuminoid
Side Effects: Constipation, diarrhea, or upset stomach may occur.

Name: Modalert
Uses: Extreme sleepiness due to narcolepsy and other sleep disorders, headache, nausea, nervousness, dizziness, or difficulty sleeping
Side Effects: Headache, nausea, nervousness, dizziness, or difficulty sleeping may occur.

Name: Biotin
Uses: Thicken hair, increase fullness, and add shine.
